description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cambridge University Hospitals (CUH) NHS Foundation Trust comprises Addenbrooke’s Hospital and the Rosie Hospital in Cambridge. With over 11000 staff and over 1100 beds the priorities of the Trust focus on a quality service which is all about people – patients, staff and partners. Recognised as providing ‘outstanding’ care to our patients and rated ‘Good’ overall by the Care Quality Commissioner, is testament to the skill and dedication of the people who work here. CUH’s values – Together- safe, kind, excellent – are at the heart of patient care, defining the way all staff work and behave. The Trust provides accessible high-quality healthcare for the local people of Cambridge, together with specialist services, dealing with rare or complex conditions for a regional, national and international population.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An exciting opportunity has become available for an enthusiastic and self-motivated individual to join the Haemophilia and Thrombophilia Non-Malignant Haematology team.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for someone with an approachable, helpful, flexible attitude who enjoys working as part of a team. You should have strong organisation and communication skills, the ability to accurately audio type, experience with data spreadsheets within Microsoft Excel and knowledge of Microsoft Office packages are essential. A comprehensive understanding of Medical terminology is also advantageous.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The role is split into two areas; Data Administration and Medical Secretary Support.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will be responsible for contributing to the management and professional administration of the databases (including HCIS and the National Haemophilia Database and to carry out a range of complex tasks relevant to job role; using EPIC alongside databases ensuring correct information is updated; to extract and provide data from databases for queries from other team members and be able compile these into reports as required.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Secretarial duties include typing clinical letters and advice and guidance within the turn-around time and dealing with patient and GP queries in a sympathetic and constructive manner, including minute typing.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;At interview stage there will be a short Excel/typing test to complete.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits to you&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer development opportunities and a wide range of benefits including on-site leisure facilities, shopping concourse, day nurseries and access to a great transport system with easy access to airports and rail travel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details of our fantastic benefits please refer to the attachment below - CUH Benefits.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note if you would like to discuss the required hours of this role further, you should approach the contact given. In some cases alternative working hours will be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We welcome applications from the Armed Forces.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dee Hobden-Deputy Operations Manager- dee.hobden@addenbrookes.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
